{
  "texts": [
    "The VIADS group received a slightly lower rating for significance and validity and a statistically significantly lower rating for feasibility regardless of the categories of hypotheses, that is, considering valid or all hypotheses, including inexperienced clinical researchers only or both.",
    "The feasibility ratings likely led to statistically significantly lower ratings when we combined the significance, validity, and feasibility ratings in the VIADS group.",
    "Meanwhile, we did notice VIADS groups generated more complex hypotheses than control groups, however, the complexity is not a measurable dimension in our current instruments.",
    "Detailed results can be found in the reference 9.",
    "Our follow-up questions focused on participants' past experiences related to hypothesis generation."
  ]
}